  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are good pranks at night?",
  "response": "Pranks should always be done with consideration and care for the well-being and feelings of others. Here are some nighttime pranks that are generally harmless and can provide some fun without causing distress:\n\n1. **Ghostly Silhouette**: Cut out a spooky silhouette (like a ghost or a monster) and tape it to the outside of a window. When someone turns on the light inside, they\u2019ll see the eerie shape.\n\n2. **Glow-in-the-Dark Messages**: Write messages on windows or mirrors using glow-in-the-dark paint or stickers. When the lights go out, the messages will appear like magic.\n\n3. **Switch Light Bulbs**: Replace normal light bulbs with colored ones in key areas of the house so when people flip the switch, they get an unexpected light show.\n\n4. **Spooky Sounds**: Hide a Bluetooth speaker somewhere and play eerie sounds or creepy noises to give someone a mild scare.\n\n5. **Fake Spiders**: Place realistic-looking fake spiders or insects in common areas like the bathroom or kitchen. When someone turns on the light, they\u2019ll get a startling surprise.\n\n6. **Silent Intruder**: Dress up in dark clothing and quietly move around the house while others are watching TV or hanging out. When they catch a glimpse of you, it will give them a mild fright.\n\n7. **Motion Sensor Lights**: Place motion sensor lights in areas where they\u2019re not expected. When someone walks by, the sudden bright light will catch them off guard.\n\n8. **Mirror Prank**: Write something with a dry-erase marker or sticky note on the bathroom mirror, such as a spooky message, so the first person who turns on the light sees it.\n\nRemember to ensure that your pranks are safe and do not cause any lasting fear or harm. Always consider the comfort and boundaries of others to make sure everyone can enjoy a good laugh.",
